'''Tahith Jose Girigorio Djorkaef Chong''' (born 4 December 1999) is a Curaçaoan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[wide midfielder]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for {{English football updater|SheffieU}} club [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] and the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

Chong joined the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United Academy]] aged 16, after progressing through the [[Feyenoord Academy (Varkenoord)|Feyenoord youth system]]. He won both the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Players of the Year|Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year]] and Denzil Haroun Reserve Player of the Year awards at United. He made his professional debut in 2019, in an [[FA Cup]] game against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]. In August 2020, he joined [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on a season-long loan, which was cut short in January 2021 to facilitate a loan move to [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]]. He spent the 2021–22 season on loan at [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]], joined the club on a four-year contract in September 2022, and moved on to [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] in July 2023. After two seasons with Luton Town, Chong signed for Sheffield United in August 2025.

Chong made more than 40 appearances for the Netherlands national youth teams from under-15 to [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|under-21]] level, before switching to Curaçao in 2025.

==Early life==
Chong was born in [[Willemstad]], [[Curaçao]], which was then part of the Netherlands Antilles. He is of Chinese descent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/634541/manchester-united-krijgt-nul-op-rekest-ik-wil-gewoon-bij-feyenoord-blijven-.html|title=Manchester United gets zero on demand: "I just want to stay at Feyenoord"|date=26 January 2016|work=Voetbal Primeur|access-date=11 January 2019|language=nl}}</ref> He was scouted by [[Feyenoord]] while playing for Atlétiko Saliña in Willemstad.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kelly |first1=Ciaran |title=Manchester United player Tahith Chong had the opposite problem to Lionel Messi |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-utd-tahith-chong-messi-14626274 |access-date=23 December 2025 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=8 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Duane Tjen-A-Kwoei van Spijkenisse heeft geen vrije zomer |url=https://voetbaljournaal.com/duane-tjen-a-kwoei-van-spijkenisse-heeft-geen-vrije-zomer/ |website=Voetbal Journaal |access-date=23 December 2025 |language=nl |date=3 June 2022 |quote=Ik heb in Willemstad gespeeld bij VV Willemstad en bij Atletiko Salina. Bij die club speelde ook Tahith Chong, voordat hij naar Feyenoord ging.}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Chong joined the youth ranks of [[Eredivisie]] club [[Feyenoord]] aged 10, and had attracted interest from several [[Premier League]] clubs by the age of 16.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.the42.ie/tahith-chong-manchester-united-2742470-Apr2016/|title=Sixteen-year-old Feyenoord wonderkid confirms Manchester United move|date=29 April 2016|work=The 42|publisher=TheJournal.ie|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> In September 2014, Chong took part in the [[Manchester Premier Cup]] at the [[Trafford Training Centre|Carrington Training Ground]], where he was spotted by [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] scouts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-utd-chelsea-tahith-chong-15657423|title = How Manchester United beat Chelsea to the signing of Tahith Chong|date = 10 January 2019}}</ref> In early 2016, Chong was on the verge of joining [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/revealed-how-man-utd-snatched-chong-from-under-the-nose-of/147b2ubukyqgw1my7g45uhqehp|title=Revealed: How Man Utd snatched Chong from under the nose of Chelsea|last=Burton|first=Chris|date=11 January 2019|website=Goal.com|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref>

===Manchester United===
====Youth====
In April 2016, Chong announced that he was to join Manchester United after Feyenoord failed to "make a plan" for him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/feyenoord-starlet-tahith-chong-confirms-11259737|title=Feyenoord starlet Tahith Chong confirms Manchester United move|last=Dixon|first=James|date=28 April 2016|work=Manchester Evening News|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> The transfer was made official three months later upon receiving international clearance.<ref name="MUFC profile">{{Cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/players-and-staff/detail/tahith-chong|title=Tahith Chong|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United|access-date=5 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220627142943/https://www.manutd.com/en/players-and-staff/detail/tahith-chong |archive-date=27 June 2022}}</ref> Initially linking up with the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Under-18s]], Chong scored his club's only goal of their [[2016–17 FA Youth Cup]] campaign as they suffered a third round exit to [[Southampton F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Southampton]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2016/12/12/tahith-chong-scores-incredible-goal-for-manchester-united-against-southampton-in-fa-youth-cup-6318706/|title=Tahith Chong scores incredible goal for Manchester United against Southampton in FA Youth Cup|last=Olver|first=Tom|date=12 December 2016|work=The Metro|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> The following month, he was ruled out for the remainder of the season after suffering a [[cruciate ligament]] injury.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-academy-news-chong-12527037|title=Manchester United starlet Tahith Chong is hit with serious injury setback|last=Mathieson|first=Stuart|date=30 January 2017|work=Manchester Evening News|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> Making his return 10 months later for the Under-23s, Chong went on to be named the Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year in May 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/tahith-chong-wins-jimmy-murphy-young-player-of-the-year-award-for-2017-18|title=Tahith Chong wins Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year award for 2017/18|last=Marshall|first=Adam|date=1 May 2018|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref>

====Senior====
In July 2018, Chong was called up to the first team for their pre-season tour in the [[United States]]. In their opening game, he featured as a second-half substitute in a 1–1 draw against [[Club América]], followed by starting in their goalless draw against the [[San Jose Earthquakes]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/match-report-man-united-v-club-america-tour-2018|title=Tour 2018 Match Report: United 1 Club America 1|last=Thompson|first=Gemma|date=20 July 2018|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/match-report-san-jose-earthquakes-v-manchester-united-in-santa-clara-tour-2018|title=Tour 2018 Match Report: San Jose Earthquakes 0 United 0|last=Thompson|first=Gemma|date=23 July 2018|website=ManUtd.com|publisher=Manchester United|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> On 23 October, he was named as an unused substitute for the first time in United's 1–0 defeat to [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45907593|title=Manchester United 0–1 Juventus|last=Bevan|first=Chris|date=23 October 2018|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> Following the appointment of [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]] as caretaker manager, Chong made his competitive debut replacing [[Juan Mata]] in a 2–0 [[FA Cup]] victory against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 5 January.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46706809|title=Manchester United 2–0 Reading|last=Davis|first=Matt|date=5 January 2019|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=11 January 2019}}</ref> At the end of the season, he was named the Denzil Haroun Reserve Player of the Year award, becoming the first player since [[Giuseppe Rossi]] to win the award the year after being named the Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Tahith Chong voted Under-23s Player of the Year |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/tahith-chong-wins-man-utd-reserve-team-player-of-the-year-2018-19 |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=9 May 2019 |access-date=10 May 2019 }}</ref> On 9 March 2020, Chong signed a new contract to keep him at the club until 2022, with the option to extend a further year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tahith Chong signs new contract with Man Utd |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/tahith-chong-signs-new-contract-with-man-utd |website=Manchester United |access-date=5 August 2020 |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>

====Werder Bremen and Club Brugge loans====
On 16 August 2020, Chong joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Bostock |title=United confirm loan move for youngster |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/manchester-united-winger-tahith-chong-joins-werder-bremen-on-loan |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=16 August 2020 |access-date=16 August 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester United's Tahith Chong completes loan to Werder Bremen |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/aug/16/tahith-chong-manchester-united-loan-to-werder-bremen |access-date=16 August 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=16 August 2020}}</ref> On 12 September, he scored his first goal in his first competitive match for Werder Bremen against [[FC Carl Zeiss Jena]] in the [[DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sargent eröffnet, Chongs Premiere: Werder in Runde zwei|url=https://www.kicker.de/jena-gegen-bremen-2020-dfb-pokal-4660441/analyse|access-date=2020-09-22|website=kicker|language=de-DE}}</ref> Chong's loan was cut short in January 2021.<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=SV Werder Bremen EN |user= werderbremen_en |number=1355600739725434885 |date=30 January 2021 |title=i️ @TahithC has ended his loan spell early and will leave SV #Werder Bremen. Thank you for all of your contributions and good luck for the future, Tahith! 💚 |access-date=30 January 2021}}</ref> Chong joined [[Belgian First Division A]] club [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] on loan on 30 January,<ref>{{cite news |title=Tahith Chong (21) wordt vijfde Nederlander bij Club Brugge |url=https://www.ad.nl/buitenlands-voetbal/tahith-chong-21-wordt-vijfde-nederlander-bij-club-brugge~aea92424/ |work=Algemeen Dagblad |date=30 January 2021 |access-date=4 February 2021 |language=nl}}</ref> and scored on his debut four days later in a [[Belgian Cup]] game against Olsa Brakel.<ref>{{cite news |title=Club bekert verder na 6–1 zege tegen Olsa Brakel |url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/nl/nieuws/club-bekert-verder-na-6-1-zege-tegen-olsa-brakel |work=Club Brugge |date=3 February 2021 |access-date=4 February 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

====Birmingham City (loan)====
On 9 July 2021, Chong joined [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Chong arrives on loan |url=https://bcfc.com/news/articles/2021/highly-rated-chong-joins-blues |work=Birmingham City F.C. |date=9 July 2021 |access-date=9 July 2021 |archive-date=9 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709153528/https://www.bcfc.com/news/articles/2021/highly-rated-chong-joins-blues/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> However, he spent pre-season ahead of the 2021–22 campaign at his parent club, and joined Birmingham in time for the start of the Championship season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Michael |last=Benson |title=Explained: Why goalscorer Tahith Chong still played for Manchester United against Derby after signing for Birmingham on loan, as fans at pre-season game come together for anti-Leeds chant |url=https://talksport.com/football/913691/tahith-chong-manchester-united-derby-birmingham-leeds/ |work=Talksport |date=18 July 2021 |access-date=18 July 2021 }}</ref> He made his debut for Birmingham in a 1–0 win over [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on 7 August,<ref>{{cite news |first=Ian |last=Woodcock |title=Relegated Sheffield United fell to defeat by Birmingham City on the opening weekend of the Championship season. |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58035720 |work=BBC |date=7 August 2021 |access-date=30 August 2021 }}</ref> and two weeks later, he made two assists in a 5–0 win over [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Scott Hogan's double crowned a sparkling display by Birmingham as they thrashed hapless Luton at Kenilworth Road for their second successive away win. |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58209742 |work=BBC |date=21 August 2021 |access-date=30 August 2021 }}</ref> On 2 November 2021, Chong returned to Manchester United for his rehabilitation following surgery on a serious groin injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bcfc.com/news/articles/2021/club-statement-tahith-chong/ |title=Club statement: Tahith Chong |website=bcfc.com |publisher=Birmingham City FC |date=2 November 2021 |access-date=3 November 2021 |archive-date=3 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103103616/https://www.bcfc.com/news/articles/2021/club-statement-tahith-chong/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He returned to Birmingham in February 2022, and two minutes into his first start after his return, away to [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]], he opened the scoring in a 2–1 win; it was his only goal for the club.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/birmingham-city-bristol-player-ratings-23299366 |title=Birmingham City player ratings vs Bristol City: Chong back with a bang as Blues win |first=Brian |last=Dick |newspaper=Birmingham Mail |date=5 March 2021 |access-date=5 March 2022}}</ref><ref name=Soccerway /> He lasted another month before a hamstring injury kept him out until the last match of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-tahith-chong-injury-23629502 |title=Manchester United youngster Tahith Chong suffers fresh injury blow in Birmingham loan spell |first=George |last=Smith |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=7 April 2021 |access-date=8 May 2022}}</ref><ref name=Soccerway />

===Birmingham City===
On 1 September 2022, Chong signed a four-year contract with [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bcfc.com/news/all/tahith-chong-is-back-at-blues |title=Tahith Chong is back at Blues |publisher=Birmingham City F.C. |date=1 September 2022 |access-date=1 September 2022}}</ref>

===Luton Town===
On 14 July 2023, Chong signed for newly-promoted Premier League side [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lutontown.co.uk/news/2023/july/tahith-is-a-hatter/ |title=Tahith Chong is a Hatter! |publisher=Luton Town F.C. |date=14 July 2023 |access-date=14 July 2023}}</ref> On 5 November 2023, he scored his first Premier League goal in a 1–1 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/67065669 |title=Luton Town 1–1 Liverpool |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 November 2023 }}</ref>

===Sheffield United===
On 29 August 2025, Chong joined [[EFL Championship]] side [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on a four-year deal after Luton were relegated the previous season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yardbarker.com/soccer/articles/former_manchester_united_midfielder_pens_four_year_deal_at_sheffield_united_what_does_he_add_to_the_blades/s1_17291_42657090|title=Former Manchester United Midfielder Pens Four-year Deal At Sheffield United; What Does He Add to the Blades?|work=YardBarker.com|first=Jake|last=Staniland|date=August 29, 2025|access-date=August 29, 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Chong played youth international football for the Netherlands at under-15,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185192/uitslagen |title=Jeugd mannen onder 15 |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-16 football team|under-16]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185191/speler/270 |title=Tahith Chong Jeugd mannen onder 16 |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|under-17]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/184965/speler/270 |title=Tahith Chong Jeugd mannen onder 17 |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|under-19]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185189/speler/270 |title=Tahith Chong Jeugd mannen onder 19 |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-20 football team|under-20]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/206598/speler/270 |title=Tahith Chong Jeugd mannen beloftenelftal |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> and [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185185/speler/270 |title=Tahith Chong Jong Oranje |website=onsoranje.nl |access-date=11 July 2022}}</ref> He played for the under-17 national team at the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] and scored the only goal in the quarter-final victory against [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|Sweden]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.talkingbaws.com/2016/05/tahith-chong-shows-manchester-united-fans-what-he-can-do-in-holland-u17-game/|title=Tahith Chong Shows Manchester United Fans What He Can Do in Holland U17 Game|last=Boyle|first=Jonny|date=16 May 2016|work=Talking Baws|access-date=11 January 2019|archive-date=12 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112095025/http://www.talkingbaws.com/2016/05/tahith-chong-shows-manchester-united-fans-what-he-can-do-in-holland-u17-game/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In June 2021, Chong accepted a call-up to the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for their [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] preliminary squad.<ref>[https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/2021-concacaf-gold-cup-preliminary-rosters-announced/ 2021 Concacaf Gold Cup preliminary rosters announced]. CONCACAF. 18 June 2021. Retrieved 31 July 2021.</ref> However, he was not included in the final squad, which subsequently withdrew from the tournament due to an outbreak of [[COVID-19]].<ref>[https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/concacaf-statement-curacao-delegation-at-2021-gold-cup/ Concacaf Statement – Curacao Delegation at 2021 Gold Cup]. CONCACAF. 9 July 2021. Retrieved 31 July 2021.</ref>

On 26 August 2025, Chong's request to switch international allegiance to Curaçao  was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|website=knowledge.fifa.com|accessdate=26 August 2025}}</ref>

